text.tspan: We start our day in the kitchen with a cup of coffee or tea.
When we work from home, we sneak back into the kitchen
a few hours later for a snack. The kitchen is the central
room in our own four walls – from early morning until late
at night. And every party ends in the kitchen – that's a
well-known fact.
Household applications such as the refrigerator, the
microwave, the rice cooker and the dishwasher are part of
everyday life. Energy efficiency and convenience compl-
ment each other ideally here. Innovative semiconductor
solutions make this possible.
Modern refrigerators, for example, are smart and
connected. Their motors are controlled by power chips,
sensors and microcontrollers. These components make
motors pleasantly silent, energy efficient and smaller.
In this way, the devices only consume as much electricity
as they actually need.

EFFICIENT AND CONVENIENT
